---
export const prerender = true;
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="process — tokyo zero design case study">
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc__head">
      <p class="doc__kicker">case study · graphic design</p>
      <h1 class="doc__title">tokyo zero — building a three-theme merch line</h1>
      <p class="doc__lede">
        Tokyo Zero is a small-drop anime merch project — 47 products, three thematic
        storefronts, one voice. Here's how the brand system, typography, and page
        architecture came together.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="sec__h">01 · voice + audience</h2>
      <p>
        The core reader is the person who already knows the reference — Panty &amp; Stocking with
        Garterbelt, Needy Streamer Overload, Genshin, HoYo, Vtubers. The brand assumes fluency
        instead of explaining. Copy is short, lowercase, punchy — closer to a Discord message
        than a marketing brochure.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="pull">
        "small drops. heavy print. character work for the people who already know."
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="sec__h">02 · three storefronts, one system</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        <div class="tile">
          <p class="tile__label">misc</p>
          <h3 class="tile__title">catalog, curated</h3>
          <p>
            The neutral hub — magazine-style catalog with numbered cards, hairline dividers,
            slate-violet accent. Serves as the anchor when the themed rooms feel too loud.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <p class="tile__label">psg</p>
          <h3 class="tile__title">candy-halftone spectacle</h3>
          <p>
            Panty &amp; Stocking pastiche — hot pink frills, halftone circles, 7-card
            product showcase on a tilted cyan slab. Loads with a slam-drop TOKYO ZERO intro.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <p class="tile__label">nso</p>
          <h3 class="tile__title">crt streamer decay</h3>
          <p>
            Needy Streamer Overload homage — chrome background, RGB-glitching popup product
            boxes, scanlines everywhere. Character sprites for Ame + KAngel anchor the hero.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="sec__h">03 · typography</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Apex Mk3</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: var(--mono);">.contact</p>
          <p class="face__role">Monospace. Titles, labels, navigation. Reads as terminal
            output — matches the "design + code" story.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Beam Visionary</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic;">from the desk.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Script. Eyebrows, brand marks. The one moment of handwriting
            in an otherwise-mechanical system.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Branding Pro</p>
          <p class="face__sample">Body copy, running text, product descriptions.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Sans. Body / product copy. Neutral, wide x-height, five weights.
            Does the invisible work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">NSO CRT</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: var(--mono); letter-spacing: 0.06em;">SIGNAL &gt; NO SYNC</p>
          <p class="face__role">Pixel bitmap. NSO theme only. Chyrons, popup labels, HUD text.
            Ties the CRT visual metaphor together.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="sec__h">04 · color</h2>
      <p>
        Base palette locks the catalog in a soft-white / slate-violet universe.
        Each themed room breaks that mold on purpose — PSG goes hot pink + cyan + gold,
        NSO goes chrome + magenta + electric blue. The themes are supposed to feel like
        walking into a different shop; the misc is the hallway between.
      </p>
      <div class="swatches">
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #f5f4f0"></span>#f5f4f0 base</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #14131a"></span>#14131a ink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #5061b9"></span>#5061b9 slate-violet</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #ff4da6"></span>#ff4da6 psg pink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #3deaff"></span>#3deaff psg cyan</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #fd7ac0"></span>#fd7ac0 nso magenta</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <h2 class="sec__h">05 · character work</h2>
      <p>
        Every product carries a hand-illustrated character. Deskmats print at 900×400mm with
        rounded corners; tapestries at 60×90cm on polyester with grommets; prints at 12×18in
        on satin card stock. The full character roster spans Genshin, Star Rail, HoYo IPs,
        Vtuber and Hololive members, and the two flagship PSG/NSO castings.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="sec sec--cta">
      <p class="sec__cta-kicker">next</p>
      <h2 class="sec__cta-h">how it ships →</h2>
      <p>
        The whole storefront runs on a serverless AWS stack provisioned with Terraform.
        <a href="/architecture/">Walk through the infrastructure</a> or
        <a href="/work/">browse the catalog</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .doc {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: clamp(48px, 8vw, 96px) clamp(24px, 6vw, 48px) clamp(48px, 8vw, 96px);
    }
    .doc__head { margin-bottom: 8vh; }
    .doc__kicker {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
    }
    .doc__title {
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
      line-height: 1.05;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin: 0 0 24px;
    }
    .doc__lede {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 620px;
    }
    .sec { margin-bottom: 8vh; }
    .sec__h {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
      padding-bottom: 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
    .sec p, .sec li {
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 0 0 16px;
    }
    .pull {
      margin: 24px 0 0;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 24px;
      margin-top: 24px;
    }
    .grid--2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .grid--3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; }
    .tile, .face {
      padding: 20px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: #fff;
    }
    .tile__label, .face__name {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }
    .tile__title {
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      margin: 0 0 12px;
      line-height: 1.1;
    }
    .tile p { font-size: 0.92rem; margin: 0; color: var(--ink-soft); }
    .face__sample {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      margin: 4px 0 14px;
      line-height: 1.1;
    }
    .face__role {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .swatches {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    .sw {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
    }
    .sw span {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 28px;
      height: 28px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
    .sec--cta {
      padding: 32px;
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      border-radius: 12px;
    }
    .sec__cta-kicker {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin: 0 0 8px;
    }
    .sec__cta-h {
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      margin: 0 0 12px;
    }
    .sec--cta p { margin: 0; }
    .sec--cta a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .grid--2, .grid--3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
